<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="80">3.2. Setting up the credit rating</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Set up a credit rating if needed. Use the credit ranking e.g. to make only certain payment methods available to customers. In the case of a negative credit ranking, you could prohibit payment on invoice, you could stop the order or determine a maximum order value that may not be exceeded.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Setting up the credit rating:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Orders » Payment » Methods</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Place a check mark next to the setting <strong>Also show inactive</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the folder <strong>International</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Click on <strong>PAYONE</strong>.<br>
→ The <strong>Settings</strong> tab will open.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Expand the <strong>Credit rating</strong> area.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Carry out the settings as desired. Pay attention to the information given in <a href="#table-setup-credit-rating-payone">Table 3</a>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
